  "createdAt": "2026-06-03T02:05:00.000Z",
  "diffSummary": "Fix duplicate outgoing messages caused by Zalo redelivering an account's own sent message through the realtime listener with a different msg_id than the send-response id (so dedupe-by-msg_id stored/rendered it twice). store/db.rs save_message now skips an outgoing insert when a recent (<=15s) outgoing row with the same (account_id, thread_id, body) already exists under a different msg_id — no duplicate row and no double thread/unread bump. Frontend src/lib/session.svelte.ts appendToBucket reconciles an incoming outgoing echo into the matching just-sent optimistic message (same thread + body within 15s), upgrading its id in place rather than adding a second bubble. A distinct outgoing message in the same thread still persists/renders. Root cause was confirmed from the live SQLite store (same body under msg_ids 7894868867250 [send response] and 7894868928111 [listener echo], 0.75s apart).",
  "changedFiles": [
    "src-tauri/src/store/db.rs",
    "src/lib/session.svelte.ts"
  ],
